---- "Jeff Stewart" <fonman4277(-at-)earthlink.net> wrote:
> I just finished before Labor Day a total resto on my '77, including
> a
> complete repaint in another color. Since I wanted to change colors
> completely, I thoroughly gutted it ( I should mention it is a Westy).
> After
> a thorough cleaning of the shell and then the repaint, I sprayed the
> interior side walls with 3M rubberized undercoating, then applied a
> self
> adhesive foil faced insulation between the ribs on the side walls.
> Then the
> original insulation went back in, then the interior. The result is
> a bus
> that is almost too quiet! I can't hear the engine as well as I am used
> to. I
> can carry on a conversation with a back seat passenger without yelling.
> My
> heating system is intact and in fairly good shape, the only addition
> being a
> blower added up front, and it works very well. My door seals are new,
> and
> the front grill vents seal when closed. All this adds up to a bus that
> is
> warmer and quieter than I ever dreamed possible.
> Jeff Stewart
> 1977 Westfalia
